      "code_changes": [
        {
          "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"api--v0.32.0\",\n      \"path\": \"apps/v1/types.go\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"client-go--v0.32.0\",\n      \"path\": \"examples/create-update-delete-deployment/main.go\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"client-go--v0.32.0\",\n      \"path\": \"examples/create-update-delete-deployment/README.md\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"client-go--v0.32.0\",\n      \"path\": \"kubernetes/typed/apps/v1/deployment.go\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"api--v0.32.0\",\n      \"path\": \"README.md\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"api--v0.32.0\",\n      \"path\": \"apps/v1/types.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Deployment\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"client-go--v0.32.0\",\n      \"path\": \"kubernetes/typed/apps/v1/deployment.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"DeploymentInterface\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The canonical patterns for deploying services in Kubernetes are distributed across three key locations:\\n\\n1. **API Type Definition**: The authoritative Deployment struct is defined in the `k8s.io/api` repository at `api--v0.32.0/apps/v1/types.go` (line 359). This is the canonical location for all Kubernetes API type definitions. The Deployment struct enables declarative updates for Pods and ReplicaSets, containing TypeMeta, ObjectMeta, Spec (DeploymentSpec), and Status (DeploymentStatus) fields.\\n\\n2. **Client-Side Code Pattern**: The canonical Go code example is located in `client-go--v0.32.0/examples/create-update-delete-deployment/main.go`. This example demonstrates the fundamental operations for managing Deployment resources: Create, List, Update, and Delete. The pattern shows:\\n   - Building a kubeconfig and creating a Kubernetes client\\n   - Accessing the typed client for Deployments via `clientset.AppsV1().Deployments(namespace)`\\n   - Creating a Deployment object with ObjectMeta, Spec, and Template configuration\\n   - Using the client interface to perform CRUD operations\\n   - Implementing retry logic for conflict handling during updates\\n\\n3. **Developer Documentation**: The deployment workflow is documented in multiple files:\\n   - `client-go--v0.32.0/examples/create-update-delete-deployment/README.md`: Explains the example program and demonstrates running the fundamental operations\\n   - `client-go--v0.32.0/examples/README.md`: Provides an overview of available examples, classifying deployment management as a \\\"Basics\\\" pattern\\n   - `api--v0.32.0/README.md`: Explains that this repository is the canonical location of Kubernetes API definitions and describes the recommended use patterns\\n\\n4. **Client Interface**: The typed client interface `DeploymentInterface` is generated in `client-go--v0.32.0/kubernetes/typed/apps/v1/deployment.go` and defines methods for Create, Update, Delete, Get, List, Watch, Patch, Apply, and Scale operations on Deployment resources.\\n\\nThese files collectively form the canonical reference architecture for service deployment patterns in Kubernetes, with the api repository serving as the source of truth for API definitions, client-go providing the Go client library implementation, and examples demonstrating the recommended usage patterns.\"\n}\n",
